---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";

const lastUpdated = "16 May 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Fleetlix"
  description="How Fleetlix and CN-DESIGN LTD handle personal data on the fleetlix.com marketing site. UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018 compliant. No analytics, no tracking, no advertising cookies."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="bg-[color:var(--color-offwhite)]">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-amber)]">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-slate)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">1. Who we are</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This website (<a href="https://fleetlix.com" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">fleetlix.com</a>) is operated by <strong>CN-DESIGN LTD</strong>, a company registered in Scotland under company number <strong>SC885094</strong>, with its registered office at Office 1, Technology House, 9 Newton Place, Glasgow, Scotland, G3 7PR. Fleetlix is a product of CN-DESIGN LTD.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For the purposes of UK data protection law, CN-DESIGN LTD is the <em>data controller</em> in respect of personal information collected through this website. We are registered with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) under registration number <strong>CSN2072529</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Our Data Protection Contact is <strong>Christopher Nicholson</strong>. For any question about this policy, or to exercise any of the rights set out below, email <a href="mailto:chris@cn-design.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">chris@cn-design.co.uk</a>. General business enquiries continue to go to <a href="mailto:contact@fleetlix.com" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">contact@fleetlix.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">2. Scope of this policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This policy explains how we handle personal information collected through the <strong>fleetlix.com marketing website</strong>. The forthcoming Fleetlix operations application — covering driver, yard, office, and maintenance workflows for our customers — will be governed by a separate privacy notice and a data-processing agreement with each customer.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">3. What information we collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">The marketing site is a static website with no sign-up, no account system, and no analytics or tracking installed. We collect:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Information you send us by email.</strong> If you contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@fleetlix.com" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">contact@fleetlix.com</a>, we receive whatever you choose to include — typically your name, email address, and the contents of your message.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Server and security logs.</strong> Our hosting provider (Cloudflare) processes routine technical information when your browser requests the site — including your IP address, the URL requested, browser user-agent, and timestamp — for the purposes of delivering the site, protecting it from abuse, and producing aggregate performance metrics. These logs are held by Cloudflare under their terms and retained for short periods.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Strictly necessary cookies.</strong> Cloudflare may set a small number of cookies that are strictly necessary for security and bot management. See our <a href="/cookies" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">Cookies Policy</a> for details.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We do not use Google Analytics, advertising tags, social-media pixels, heatmaps, or any other marketing or behavioural-tracking technology on this website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">4. How and why we use information</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>To respond to enquiries you send us by email.</li>
            <li>To follow up about pilot opportunities, product demos, or commercial discussions you have initiated with us.</li>
            <li>To operate and secure the website and prevent abuse.</li>
            <li>To comply with our legal obligations (for example, retaining business correspondence for accounting purposes).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">5. Legal bases for processing</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Under UK GDPR we rely on the following lawful bases:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — to respond to enquiries you have sent us, to operate the website, and to keep it secure. We have considered your rights and freedoms and consider these interests to be balanced and unsurprising.</li>
            <li><strong>Consent</strong> — where you have explicitly opted in (for example, if you ask to be added to a mailing list). You may withdraw consent at any time.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — where we are required to retain records for tax, accounting, or other statutory purposes.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">6. Who we share information with</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information. We share information only with trusted processors who help us operate the business:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li><strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> — hosting, content delivery, and security for the website (acting as a data processor on our behalf).</li>
            <li><strong>Email provider</strong> — the provider that hosts the <code>contact@fleetlix.com</code> inbox processes correspondence on our behalf so we can read and reply.</li>
            <li><strong>Professional advisers</strong> — accountants and legal advisers where strictly necessary.</li>
            <li><strong>Law-enforcement or regulatory bodies</strong> — where we are required to disclose information by law.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">7. International transfers</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Cloudflare operates a global content-delivery and security network. As a result, technical information about your visit (such as your IP address) may be processed at Cloudflare points of presence outside the United Kingdom and European Economic Area. Cloudflare relies on UK and EU standard contractual clauses and equivalent safeguards for those transfers. You can read Cloudflare's privacy practices at <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]" rel="noopener" target="_blank">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">8. How long we keep information</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li><strong>Email correspondence</strong> — retained for as long as the commercial relationship or enquiry is active, and for up to six years thereafter in line with UK accounting record-keeping requirements.</li>
            <li><strong>Server logs</strong> — retained by Cloudflare for short periods under their own retention schedule.</li>
            <li><strong>Strictly necessary cookies</strong> — expire automatically; see our <a href="/cookies" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">Cookies Policy</a>.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">9. Your rights</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Under UK GDPR you have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you (right of access).</li>
            <li>Ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete information (right to rectification).</li>
            <li>Ask us to delete information we hold about you, in certain circumstances (right to erasure).</li>
            <li>Ask us to restrict how we use your information, in certain circumstances.</li>
            <li>Object to our processing where we are relying on legitimate interests.</li>
            <li>Receive a copy of your information in a portable format, where applicable.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time, where consent is the lawful basis.</li>
            <li>Not be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing — we do not carry out any such processing on the marketing site.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To exercise any of these rights, email our Data Protection Contact at <a href="mailto:chris@cn-design.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">chris@cn-design.co.uk</a>. We will respond within one month.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">10. Complaints</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal information, please contact us first so we can put it right. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK's data-protection regulator: <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]" rel="noopener" target="_blank">ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">11. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We may update this policy from time to time. Where changes are material we will say so at the top of the page. The "Last updated" date above always reflects the most recent revision.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">12. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            CN-DESIGN LTD<br />
            Office 1, Technology House, 9 Newton Place<br />
            Glasgow, Scotland, G3 7PR<br />
            Company number: SC885094<br />
            ICO registration: CSN2072529<br />
            Data Protection Contact: Christopher Nicholson — <a href="mailto:chris@cn-design.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">chris@cn-design.co.uk</a><br />
            General enquiries: <a href="mailto:contact@fleetlix.com" class="underline hover:text-[color:var(--color-graphite)]">contact@fleetlix.com</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</Base>
